This junction is OK for small networks of 5 or so short trains.

[[File:en/Community/Junctionary/Basic4.png|none|frame|Simplest 4-way junction]]

===Pros===
*Cheap and easy to build.
*Trains don't have to slow down to climb a slope.
 
===Cons===
*Can only handle one train at a time.
*Will cause traffic-jams. 
*Trains must slow down for sharp turns. Making the corners wider make traffic-jams more likely

